Reasoning: The paper discusses the benefits of incorporating visualizations into digital collections to enhance searches and browsing, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving search functionality. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is also relevant as the paper discusses the development of a user-friendly tool for searching and visualizing historical documents. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the benefits of visualizations for browsing and exploring digital collections. cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of a tool for organizing and presenting data. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques to extract data from historical documents.
